OL,6,F"I've always put the city of Liverpool
OL,7,Fand it's people first and will always
OL,8,Fcontinue to do so. So I'll look
OL,9,Fforward to getting the opportunity to
OL,10,Fgo to court and actually clear my
OL,11,Fname."
OL,13,FJoe Anderson speaks to reporters
OL,14,Foutside of court
OL,16,FHis son David Anderson, 37, of
OL,17,FWavertree, faces a charge with
OL,18,Fconspiracy to commit misconduct in a
OL,19,Fpublic office which he denies.
